cmake-modules-webos
------------------------------------------
cmake-modules-webos extends your CMake installation with a set of functions and
macros that are required to build the majority of those Open webOS components
which use CMake for configuration.

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  ninja-1.10.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/FreeWebOS/cmake-modules-webos

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/FreeWebOS/cmake-modules-webos/archive/submissions/19.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cmake-modules-webos-19-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cmake-modules-webos-19-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cmake-modules-webos-19-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cmake-modules-webos-19-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cmake-modules-webos)
  /usr/lib/cmake/webOS/LegacyDefines.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/webOS/webOS.cmake
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cmake-modules-webos.README
  /usr/share/doc/cmake-modules-webos/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/cmake-modules-webos/REFERENCE.md

------------------

